[UII] Ensure Fleet tours are shown one at a time using a central manager (#231716)

## Summary

Resolves #220892. This PR fixes an issue where multiple Fleet tours
could display simultaneously on the agents list page, causing visual
overlap. The tours on this page generally introduce new agent management
features. We will probably add more similar tours over time, so we need
a way to ensure that they do not appear all at the same time.

Currently, in the worst case scenario, up to four tours could be shown
at the same time on this page: auto-upgrade agents, agent CSV export,
inactive agents status filter, and agent activity.

This PR adds `TourManagerProvider` context which is used by Fleet's
existing `useDismissableTour`, together creating a central tour
management system so that only one of these tours show at a given time.
The above four tours have been refactored to use this pattern.

![Aug-13-2025
16-37-35](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e0f4d600-0e02-4e52-81ec-a392092f8b1d)

### Dev notes
Note that *not all* Fleet tours should this pattern. One-off
popovers/tours that are triggered from user action will likely not need
to be coordinated with other tours (like the existing
`AddAgentHelpPopover` tour). They can use `useDismissableTour` without
trigger `setActiveTour` on themselves. On the other hand, tours
introducing new features, especially on the agent list page, probably
*should* use this.

While working on this I also thought about [EUI's guided
tours](https://eui.elastic.co/docs/components/display/tour/#guided-tour)
concept. I concluded that having "steps" is not appropriate for our use
case because 1) introducing new features is standalone, and 2) most of
our tours are dynamic, requiring certain conditions to be met before
being shown.

## Testing
- Wiping local storage in Dev Tools > Application will be helpful
- Adding fake agents via script will also be helpful: `node
scripts/create_agents --count 50 --status online --kibana
http://localhost:5601/<basePath>`
- Test various conditions for the four tours on agent list page
- Letting the fake agents go into inactive will trigger the inactive
agents status filter tour
- Performing bulk action on the fake agents (like reassign) will trigger
agent activity tour

[ResponseOps] Allow tasks to indicate they should disable themselves after run (#230998)

resolves https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/228306
resolves https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/227894

Adds the capability of a task to disable itself after running, by
returning an indication in the task response. We then use this with
alerting to allow a rule's task to disable itself if it ran but found
the rule itself was disabled.

Specifically:
- A rule throwing an error with a new reason
`RuleExecutionStatusErrorReasons.Disabled` will cause the alerting task
runner to return to task manager with a new flag `shouldDisableTask:
true`.
- During the post processing of the task, if the task indicated it
should disable itself via the new flag, it will log a warning that it's
going to do that, and then update the task with `enabled: false`.

Task store has been updated as well, to use `overwrite: true` when doing
`bulkSchedule`, as this code currently assumes that - at this point -
the task doc does not exist, so the bulk update fails with a conflict if
one does.

Specifically, when users asked questions like "how many democrats live on Dryden Road in Bernardsville?", the system would convert "democrats" to "Democratic" instead of the correct database value "DEMOCRAT". The fix involves three key changes: 1. **Enhanced system prompt** with explicit schema constraints for the `demo_party` field 2. **Intelligent field mappings** to handle common party name variations 3. **Improved SQL transformation logic** to properly handle quoted string value replacements ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human ** Critical Testing Required (3 items)** - [ ] **Test the original problematic query**: Submit "how many democrats live on Dryden Road in Bernardsville?" in the Streamlit app and verify the generated SQL uses `demo_party = 'DEMOCRAT'` instead of `demo_party = 'Democratic'` - [ ] **Verify existing functionality**: Test other party-related queries (e.g., "how many Republicans are in Somerset County?") to ensure they still work correctly and generate proper SQL - [ ] **Test edge cases**: Try variations like "Democratic voters", "republican party", "Independent voters" to ensure the field mappings handle different capitalizations and word forms correctly **Recommended Test Plan:** 1. Start the Streamlit app: `streamlit run agents/nj_voter_chat_adk/app_streamlit.py` 2. Test the original query and check the debug output in terminal for the generated SQL 3. Try several variations of party names with different capitalizations 4.
